article.headline: Princeton 57, Manhattan 45
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Kyle Koncz scored all 13 of his points in the second half to help Princeton beat Manhattan 57-45 on Wednesday night. Marcus Schroeder added 10 points and Justin Conway had eight for the Tigers (3-1) in their third straight victory. Arturo Dubois scored 14 points and Antoine Pearson had seven for the Jaspers (2-2). The Tigers shot 80 percent from the field in the second half, including 5-of-6 from 3-point range. Manhattan jumped to a 16-5 lead and, boosted by Dubois' 10 points, led 20-14 at halftime. Princeton earned its first lead after the break at 31-30 when Matt Strittmatter hit a 3-pointer with 11:02 left. Dubois' basket with 9:10 remaining netted the Jaspers their last lead at 34-33. A 3-point shot by Schroeder at 8:42 put the Tigers ahead to stay at 36-34. Koncz, who hit all three of his 3-point attempts in the second half, made a 3-pointer with 5:03 to go to put Princeton ahead 41-34.
